boat destroyer Scharfsch      tze, the scout ship Novara
and the destroyer Ozepel, all of the Austrian navy, came to
the assistance of the S-20 and also received salvos from the
Italian land batteries. But on the same day the Italian destroyer
Turbine, while scouting gave chase to an Austrian destroyer
and the Austrian cruiser Helgoland. The strength of these
Austrian ships was too much for the Turbine and she put
on speed with the intention of escaping from their fire, but she
was severely damaged by Austrian shells, and not having enough
