large were the Karlsruhe and Kronprinz Wilhelm. But
on the 1st of April, 1915, the Macedonia, a converted liner
which since November, 1914, had been interned at Las Palmas, Canary
Islands, succeeded in slipping out of the harbor laden with provisions
and supplies for use of warships and made her way to South American
waters in spite of the fact that she had run through lines patrolled
by British cruisers.



The Kronprinz Wilhelm's career as a raider ended on April
11, 1915, when, like the Prinz Eitel Friedrich, she succeeded
in getting past the British cruisers and slipped into Newport News,
Virginia. How this former Hamburg-American liner had slipped out
of the harbor of New York on the night of August 3, 1914, with her
bunkers and even her cabins filled with coal and provisions, with all
