the Austrians and Germans previously described. Along the San the
troops just south of Ewarts delivered a fierce attack and drove
the Archduke Ferdinand back to Tarnobrzeg on the Vistula. Ivanoff
next drew as many reenforcements from that flank to strengthen his
center as was compatible with safety. What had happened meanwhile on
Ivanoff's Page 1499
