way through Grajewo, toward Augustowo, the center of the troops
of General von B      low for several days fought the Russians in
furious battle in the vicinity of Lyck. From all sides the Germans
were closing in. To protect the withdrawal of this main army to
Suwalki and Augustowo, the Russians endeavored by all means to
hold the narrows of the lakes before Lyck, where they were favored
by the nature of the ground and aided by strong defensive works,
for the most part well provided with wire entanglements. The best
